metadata.name: A Dream of Home: Wash Day
metadata.description:
‘A Dream of Home’ 

I close my eyes and count to ten 
I take a breath and I open them 
Jucking board, breeze blocks on the ground,
it smells just like home as I look around.
Skinned football by concrete blocks
clothing line to hang my socks,
broken fence behind the latrine,
this feels like home but it’s just a dream.


A collaborative piece put together by Mahogany Culture Collective as part of a physical installation. 

Zoe Osborne 
Ayanna Nash
Fxrstnxme 
Nya-Krystien Greene 

https://www.mahoganyculture.com/adream
